# Flight Club Schedule Architecture Blueprint

## Core Principle
The monthly schedule screen is the final
polished crew summary of a normalized schedule
model — never a direct rendering of imported HTML.

## 10-Layer Architecture

### Layer 1 — FLICA Import (DO NOT TOUCH)
- WebView login, cookies, token capture
- Files: import-flica-direct.tsx,
  flicaScheduleService.ts
- Status: WORKING — never modify without approval

### Layer 2 — Raw Parser (DO NOT TOUCH)
- Extracts table rows, cells, D-END boundaries
- Assigns dutyPeriodDate from D-END groups
- File: flicaScheduleHtmlParser.ts
- Status: WORKING — never modify without approval

### Layer 3 — Row Classifier
- Classifies each parsed row as:
  TRIP_HEADER, REPORT_ROW, LEG_ROW,
  LAYOVER_ROW, RELEASE_ROW, TOTALS_ROW,
  DEND_ROW, OFF_ROW, NON_FLIGHT_ROW
- Input: raw FlicaLeg[] from parser
- Output: ClassifiedRow[]

### Layer 4 — Date Resolver
- Uses dutyPeriodDate from parser as source of truth
- Never moves dates based on departure time
- Handles month crossing for carry-in/carry-out
- Handles midnight legs via dutyPeriodDate
- NO post-processing alignment of any kind

### Layer 5 — Trip Normalizer
- Groups classified rows into Trip objects
- Each Trip has DutyDay[]
- Each DutyDay has Leg[]
- Attaches layovers to correct DutyDay
- Calculates touchedDays[]

### Layer 6 — Persistence
- Upserts normalized trips to Supabase
- schedule_pairings table = Trip
- schedule_duties table = DutyDay (NEW)
- schedule_pairing_legs table = Leg
- Deduplication via upsert

### Layer 7 — Classic Display Builder
- Reads from normalized model only
- Never reads raw HTML rows
- Builds ClassicScheduleRow per calendar day
- Row types: EMPTY_DAY, TRIP_START,
  TRIP_CONTINUATION, TRIP_END,
  CARRY_IN, CARRY_OUT, NON_FLIGHT_DUTY

### Layer 8 — UI Renderer
- Table layout only
- No parsing logic
- Tap navigation to detail screens

### Layer 9 — Detail Renderer
- Full trip/leg details
- Report/release/totals/hotels

### Layer 10 — Overlay Services
- Weather, hotel, flight tracker,
  crew assistant, legality

## Data Model

### Trip/Pairing
- pairingId: string
- tripStartDateIso: string
- tripEndDateIso: string
- touchedDays: string[]
- baseAirport: string
- reportTime: string
- dutyDays: DutyDay[]

### DutyDay
- dutyDateIso: string (from D-END boundary)
- reportTime: string
- dutyOffTime: string
- legs: Leg[]
- layoverCity: string | null
- layoverTime: string | null
- isContinuation: boolean
- isOvernightDuty: boolean

### Leg
- dutyDateIso: string (same as parent DutyDay)
- actualDepDateIso: string (from HTML DD column)
- flightNumber: string
- depAirport: string
- arrAirport: string
- depTimeLocal: string
- arrTimeLocal: string
- crossesMidnight: boolean
- isDeadhead: boolean

### ClassicScheduleRow
- dateIso: string
- pairingText: string | null (first day only)
- reportText: string | null
- cityText: string | null
- dutyEndText: string | null
- layoverText: string | null
- rowType: RowType

## J3H95 Test Case (source of truth)
Pairing J3H95 Apr 22-24:
- DutyDay 1: Apr 22 — JFK-LAS, LAS-BOS
  layoverCity=BOS layoverTime=2355
- DutyDay 2: Apr 23 — BOS-LAS (dep 1926),
  LAS-JFK (dep 0009, dutyPeriodDate=Apr23)
  isOvernightDuty=true
- Apr 24 — continuation arrival day
  cityText=JFK no report no D-END

Classic list must show:
W22 J3H95 0500 BOS  1817 2355
T23        1812 -   0741
F24            JFK

## Hard Rules
1. dutyPeriodDate from parser is ALWAYS
   the duty date. Never override it.
2. Never render raw HTML rows in month view.
3. Never delete existing working import files.
4. Never delete existing Supabase tables
   without explicit approval.
5. Always test J3H95 case before any
   display changes.
